Vice President Kamala Harris visited Hampton University in Virginia and spoke about the importance of Historically Black Colleges and Universities (HBCUs). She praised Hampton University for its partnership with NASA and highlighted the achievements of HBCU graduates in the fields of science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM). Harris emphasized the need to invest in HBCUs to support research and development, upgrade facilities, and increase diversity in STEM fields. She also discussed the impact of artificial intelligence and the importance of ensuring diverse perspectives in machine learning. Harris concluded by emphasizing the importance of self-determination and the role of HBCUs in promoting full participation in society.